title: Rochester's heritage society hosts fashion show
text:
Rochester's heritage society hosts fashion show 0 comments 
ROCHESTER -- The Rochester Area Heritage Society will debut its free Travel through Times Historical Series on Oct. 21 with a free fashion show of Victorian and Eastern Woodlands Native American dress. 
Brenda Applegate, executive director of the Beaver County Historical Research and Landmarks Foundation, designed the show featuring clothing in the styles of both periods. She will narrate the fashion show and intertwine history of the clothing and times. 
Applegate also will share history about the Vicary House in Freedom, home of the research and landmarks foundation. 
The 7 p.m. show is free and will be in the auditorium of the municipal building on Adams Street. 
Guests also are invited to tour the heritage society's Vintage Room, which spotlights clothing from the late 1800s from prominent Rochester families, historic glassware and other town artifacts. 
Information: 724-777-7697.
